auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 32w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_48,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 48w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_64,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 64w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_96,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 96w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_128,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 128w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_256,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 256w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_384,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 384w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_640,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 640w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_750,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 750w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_828,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 828w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1080,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 1080w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1200,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 1200w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_1920,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 1920w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_2048,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 2048w, https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg 3840w\" src=\"https://www.autoblog.com/.image/w_3840,q_auto:good,c_limit/NzowMDAwMDAwMDAwODk1NTU3/240227_eric_anderson_2880x1920_9_y3qsg9-895557.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\n            \n        \n\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eRising costs could kill or delay the launch of affordable EVs in the $25,000 range — models that are crucial for mass adoption. “Any delay in low-cost EV models will also materially set back charging infrastructure deployment,” said Koenig.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"final-thoughts\"\u003eFinal thoughts\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eWith more than 208,000 public EV charging ports currently online, the U.S. still lags far behind what’s needed to support projected EV adoption by 2030. BNEF estimates that nearly 174,000 new charging points need to be added every year just to stay on track, assuming no new policies are introduced.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003cp data-wp-block=\"{\u0026#34;dropCap\u0026#34;:false}\" data-wp-block-name=\"core/paragraph\"\u003eWithout continued federal support, experts warn, EV infrastructure could fall dangerously short, discouraging new buyers and risking a major setback in the transition away from fossil fuels.\u003c/p\u003e\n            \n        \n\n\n\n\u003csection\u003e\u003carticle\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003ca aria-label=\"View post: 2025 Q7: Is It Worth \u0026amp;#x24;60,500? My In-Depth Guide to Its Upsides \u0026amp;amp;amp; Downsides\" tabindex=\"-1\" href=\"https://www.autoblog.com/reviews/2025-audi-q7-is-it-worth-60500\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"2025 Audi Q7\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(min-width: 790px) 375px, (min-width: 768px) calc(50vw - 24px), calc(100v